# Custom AI Agent Rules for Project

## General Guidelines
- Ensure that all contributions align with the project's overall goals and architectural principles.
- Follow the defined coding standards and documentation practices diligently.

## Specific Instructions

### API Endpoints
- Always document new API endpoints in the `API_REFERENCE.md` file with detailed examples and error handling.
- Ensure proper use of HTTP status codes and provide standardized error responses.

### Testing
- Write comprehensive unit tests for any new functionality. Tests should be placed in the `tests/` directory and follow the convention used in existing tests.

### Documentation
- Use Google-style docstrings for all new functions and classes.
- Update the README or relevant documentation sections whenever a significant change is made.

### Collaboration
- Collaborate effectively using pull requests, ensuring code reviews are conducted for all changes.
- Engage with the community through issue discussions and feedback to facilitate shared learning.

### Frontend Integration
- Plan for future frontend expansion by ensuring backend endpoints are flexible and well-defined.

### Security & Maintenance
- Regularly check for and address any security vulnerabilities in the dependencies and code.
- Refactor code for maintainability and clarity when necessary, keeping in mind the overall design patterns of the application.

### Use of AI Tools
- Use AI-assisted tools to enhance productivity, ensuring that suggestions are reviewed and adapted to fit the codebase standards.

By adhering to these rules, contributions will help maintain the quality and progression of the project effectively.